# Lumi - App Flow, Pages, and User Roles

## User Roles

- **User:** Journaling customer
- **Admin (internal):** Developer/admin view of system health & stats

## Core Pages

### Landing Page
- AI-generated fantasy scene
- Title, tagline ("a daily moment of reflection")
- Login/Signup buttons

### Journal Page (Home)
- Daily AI-generated advice (personalized)
- "Journal Now" (audio capture via browser)
- Transcript history with AI questions interwoven
- Export options (PDF/Excel)
- Placeholder for printed journal purchase

### Call Settings Page
- Set daily call time
- Missed call retry rules (up to 3 retries/day)
- Phone number entry & channel selection (Phone/WhatsApp)

### Subscription Page
- Pricing display ($33/month or $333/year)
- Option to purchase your journal entries as a printed book for $100 (button is grayed out as this is not available yet)
- Stripe-managed customer portal

### Admin Dashboard (Internal Only)
- Call success rates, durations, journaling frequency stats
- System health overview
- No access to user transcripts post-development

## App Flow

1. **Onboarding**
   - User signs up onto 7-day free trial
   - Sets call schedule and phone number
   - Chooses subscription plan
   - After 7-day trial ends, if user does not subscribe to a paid plan, Lumi no longer calls user and Lumi no longer provides prompts. Free version is simply a web-app that records and transcribes entries.

2. **Daily Use Flow**
   - Lumi calls at scheduled time (or user journals manually)
   - Audio transcribed in real-time via AssemblyAI
   - Transcript analyzed by AI → daily advice generated
   - Advice shown on Journal Page post-call

3. **Personalization Flow**
   - Personalization state updated after each journal
   - AI adapts prompts and reflections accordingly
   - Longitudinal growth insights evolve over time

